      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WHAT A WROUGHT (4) had been super consistent recording three placings in a row before he was rewarded with a win last time, scoring at this track over 435m (24.59). Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings two times from three attempts. Great chance to get the job done again. PETITE BEAST (1) missed the frame last time when fifth (25.16) at this track in a Grade 5 but not beaten far the start prior. Can improve sharply here. YORKSHIRE GIRL (2) turned in a better effort at Warragul last start, finishing third behind Urana Taurus (26.52) in a T3 RSTW. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Can measure up. NICKED AGAIN (6) placed last time (25.10) at this track in a Bottom Up - Grade 5, finishing third and beaten 5.5 lengths. Has two wins already from this draw.",
